reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Value Notebooks
reviews.reviewText: My son and I like this one-subject spiral notebook for different reasons.My son- Does NOT have the annoying blue triangles to the left of the red line that you see in the “Five Star” brand pages.Me- Good value price for a one-subject notebookOther excellent things about the notebook:1) Front cover AND the inside pocket folder are both plastic- good for longevity. In the Five Star brand, it’s a mere paper folder.2) Pages are perforated for tear out and are college-ruled. Each page is standard 8.5” X 11”.3) 100 sheets of paper4) Note the ends of the spiral wire are bent inwards. No more snagging other stuff in your backpack.5) Three holes fit easily inside a 3-ring binder (make sure it’s at least a 2 inch binder).6) Great value price for one notebook. Pages are of good thickness for writing with pen or pencil.Conclusion: Excellent value one-subject notebook. Some advantages over Five Star brand as mentioned above. It’s even cheaper for one notebook, if you buy a pack of three. Going to buy these from now on to save money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple notebook for school or journaling
reviews.reviewText: Overall, this seems like a basic notebook that you can get at any brick store for school shopping. Nothing spectacular in terms of the cover or pages. It does what it says and gives you what you expect. The only two things that came to mind in terms of comparison shopping is that a positive is that it has 100 pages, most I've seen in the past have 60-75 pages, so this has a bit more. The negative is that even though this has more pages, it seems pricey - at $7 for 1 or $17 for 3, this seems high compared to others being sold on the same site.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice price, good product
reviews.reviewText: I've never heard of this brand but have 2 kids in high school so will be buying notebooks for years to come. Got this single, 1 subject notebook the other day. It's nice, with pockets inside and good for a single subject. It is as described, and think it's a good price for what you get.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 15, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I enjoy this notebook and like the plastic cover with the added folders. The pages tear easily and I like that it has 100 pages which makes it slightly larger then other notebooks of the same size. It is sturdy and will be great for my class.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Standard size with good paper quality
reviews.reviewText: The notebook is standard size with ruled pages. The binding on the outside is not too heavy and protects the notebook from tearing or bending. The pages are smooth quality and the spiral spine keeps them together.

reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Good quality and value. Classic blue color which I like, and it has a good page amount 100 pages. The size really works for me, and the value just adds to the overall value of this notebook.
